gene sets

a bit more detail info on collections:
https://www.gsea-msigdb.org/gsea/msigdb/collection_details.jsp

hallmark

hallmark <- gmtPathways("h.all.v7.4.symbols.gmt")

this is the Hallmark set, which is kind of a meta set derived from multiple other sets in the MSigDB that reduces redundancy
https://www.cell.com/cell-systems/fulltext/S2405-4712(15)00218-5

cannonical

c2_cannonical <- gmtPathways("c2.cp.v7.4.symbols.gmt")

this is the canonical pathways subset of the c2 collection:
https://www.gsea-msigdb.org/gsea/msigdb/genesets.jsp?collection=CP

it includes the BIOCARTA, WIKIPATHWAYS, REACTOME, KEGG, and PID are three different collections
BIOCARTA: https://maayanlab.cloud/Harmonizome/dataset/Biocarta+Pathways (seems old)
WIKIPATHWAYS: https://www.wikipathways.org/index.php/WikiPathways REACTOME: https://reactome.org/ KEGG: Kyoto Encyclopedia of Genes and Genomes: https://www.genome.jp/kegg/
PID: Pathway Interaction Database: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/18832364/ (seems old)

ontology

c5_ontology <- gmtPathways("c5.all.v7.4.symbols.gmt")

entire c5 collection described as ontology gene sets https://www.gsea-msigdb.org/gsea/msigdb/genesets.jsp?collection=C5
GO (gene ontology) gene sets: http://amigo.geneontology.org/amigo
GO:BP (GO biological process, 7481 gene sets)
GO:CC (GO cellular component, 996 gene sets)
GO:MF (GO molecular function, 1708 gene sets)
and
HPO (Human Phenotype Ontology, 4813 gene sets): https://hpo.jax.org/app/

CoMMpass spectra associated with survival outcomes

the following spectra are significant in the CoxPH model
OS: Sp2 + Sp3 + Sp4 + Sp5 + Sp9 + Sp12 + Sp13 + Sp19 + Sp26
PFS: Sp1 + Sp2 + Sp4 + Sp5 + Sp9 + Sp11 + Sp24 + Sp26 + Sp32
TTF: Sp1 + Sp2 + Sp4 + Sp5 + Sp9 + Sp10 + Sp18 + Sp24 + Sp31 + Sp32

unique spectra list: Sp1, Sp2, Sp3, Sp4, Sp5, Sp9, Sp10, Sp11, Sp12, Sp13, Sp18, Sp19, Sp24, Sp26, Sp31, Sp32

fgsea needs preranked vector with names where names are gene names

Hallmark pathways

gsea_results <- data.frame()
set.seed(5413)
for(s in paste0("Sp", 1:39)){
  nspl <- cmps_spec_rm_wn[,s] %>% pull(s)
  names(nspl) <- cmps_spec_rm_wn$gene_name
  nspl <- sort(nspl, decreasing=T)
  fgsea_hm <- fgsea(pathways = hallmark,
                  stats = nspl,
                  eps=0)
  gsea_results <- bind_rows(gsea_results, 
                            fgsea_hm %>% filter(padj<0.000025) %>% arrange(padj) %>% mutate(spectra=s))
}
gsea_results_sm <- gsea_results %>% select(spectra, pathway, padj, NES, size, leadingEdge)

using categories from table 1 from the Hallmark paper (Liberzon et al 2015, http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/j.cels.2015.12.004)

gsea_results_sm <- gsea_results_sm %>% 
  mutate(func_gr=case_when(pathway=="HALLMARK_UV_RESPONSE_UP" ~ "DNA damage",
                           pathway=="HALLMARK_APICAL_JUNCTION" ~ "cellular component",
                           pathway %in% c("HALLMARK_COMPLEMENT","HALLMARK_INTERFERON_ALPHA_RESPONSE",
                                          "HALLMARK_INTERFERON_GAMMA_RESPONSE", "HALLMARK_INFLAMMATORY_RESPONSE"
                                          ) ~ "immune",
                           pathway %in% c("HALLMARK_ANDROGEN_RESPONSE", "HALLMARK_IL2_STAT5_SIGNALING", 
                                          "HALLMARK_KRAS_SIGNALING_UP", "HALLMARK_MTORC1_SIGNALING",
                                          "HALLMARK_TNFA_SIGNALING_VIA_NFKB"
                                          ) ~ "signaling",
                           pathway %in% c("HALLMARK_E2F_TARGETS", "HALLMARK_G2M_CHECKPOINT", 
                                          "HALLMARK_MYC_TARGETS_V1", "HALLMARK_MYC_TARGETS_V2", 
                                          "HALLMARK_P53_PATHWAY", "HALLMARK_MITOTIC_SPINDLE" 
                                          ) ~ "proliferation",
                           pathway %in% c("HALLMARK_APOPTOSIS", "HALLMARK_HYPOXIA", 
                                          "HALLMARK_UNFOLDED_PROTEIN_RESPONSE") ~ "pathway",
                           pathway %in% c("HALLMARK_OXIDATIVE_PHOSPHORYLATION", "HALLMARK_HEME_METABOLISM") ~ "metabolic"))
gsea_results_sm$func_gr <- factor(gsea_results_sm$func_gr,

plot padj with color as sign of NES

gsea_results_plt <- gsea_results_sm %>% 
  separate(spectra, into=c(NA,"spnum"), sep=2) %>% 
  mutate(spnum=as.numeric(spnum)) %>% 
  mutate(siglvl=case_when(padj <= 1e-12 ~ 5, 
                          padj > 1e-12 & padj <= 1e-10 ~ 4,
                          padj > 1e-10 & padj <= 1e-8 ~ 3, 
                          padj > 1e-8 & padj <= 1e-6 ~ 2,
                          padj > 1e-6 & padj <= 2.5e-5 ~ 1)) %>% 
  mutate(siglvl=case_when(NES<0 ~ -siglvl, 
                             NES>0 ~ siglvl)) %>%  
  mutate(dir=case_when(NES<0 ~ -1, 
                       NES>0 ~ 1))
gsea_results_plt$pathway <- gsub("HALLMARK_", "", gsea_results_plt$pathway)
gsea_results_plt$func_gr <- factor(gsea_results_plt$func_gr,

unique_gene_results <- data.frame()
for (p in sig_paths) {
  tempd <- gsea_results_sm %>% filter(pathway==p) %>% select(spectra, leadingEdge)
  temp_sp <- tempd$spectra
  for (s in temp_sp) {
    temp_lel <- list(tempd %>% filter(spectra==s) %>% pull(leadingEdge) %>% unlist(), 
                     tempd %>% filter(spectra!=s) %>% pull(leadingEdge) %>% unlist())
    temp_ugl <- Reduce(setdiff, temp_lel)
    unique_gene_results <- bind_rows(unique_gene_results,
                                     data.frame(spectra=s, pathway=p, n_unique_genes=length(temp_ugl),
                                                unique_genes=paste(temp_ugl, collapse = ",")))
  }
}
# write_csv(unique_gene_results, "test_unique_gene_summary_20221214.csv")
common_gene_results <- data.frame()
for (p in sig_paths) {
  tempd <- gsea_results_sm %>% filter(pathway==p) %>% select(spectra, leadingEdge)
  temp_sp <- tempd$spectra
  temp_cgl <- Reduce(intersect, as.list(tempd$leadingEdge))
  common_gene_results <- bind_rows(common_gene_results,
                                     data.frame(pathway=p, spectra=paste(temp_sp, collapse = ","), 
                                                n_common_genes=length(temp_cgl),
                                                common_genes=paste(temp_cgl, collapse = ",")))
}
